         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: (and who) has attained (the diminution of hatred) [TB]: and who has (attained the diminution) of hatred</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: [and] crushed (the thorns of village [life])</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: (he) is (verily) called a monk</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB]: scoldings, (killings and binding)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: who (does not) stagger (because of happiness and sorrow), he is a monk</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB]: (he who has not gone too far), nor (clung) too much</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT]: (that) monk gives up this world</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht1327"/>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>446-447</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>140-141</citedRange></bibl></note><note corresp="#a1 #a2 #b3 #b4" type="philcomment">A little piece is probably wrongly attached to the left; it is not considered in the transliteration.</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.32.49c <hi>yaś ca dveṣakṣayaṃ prāptaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.32.50b <hi>marditā grāmakaṇṭakāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.32.50d <hi>sa vai bhikṣur nirucyate</hi></note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">Uv.32.54b <hi>hy ākrośāś ca vadhāś ca bandhanaṃ ca</hi></note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">of the <hi>k</hi> only minimal rests can be seen. If <hi>nākälñe</hi> /nákəlńe/ ‘reproach’ has a pl. <hi>nakalñenta</hi> /nakə́lńenta/, we could nevertheless equate <hi>ākrośāś ca</hi> and identify it as Uv. 32.54b.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.32.54d <hi>sukhaduḥkhena na vethate sa bhikṣuḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.32.55a <hi>yo nātyasaraṃ na cātyalīyaṃ</hi></note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.32.55c <hi>sa tu bhikṣur idaṃ jahāty apāraṃ</hi></note></p>
         </div>
